58// Field trial which controls whether to report standard-compliant bytes
59// sent/received per stream. If enabled, padding and headers are not included
60// in bytes sent or received.
61constexpr char kUseStandardBytesStats[] = "WebRTC-UseStandardBytesStats";
62
63// The following is the enum RTCStatsIceCandidateType from
64// http://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#rtcstatsicecandidatetype-enum such that
65// our stats report for ice candidate type could conform to that.
66const char STATSREPORT_LOCAL_PORT_TYPE[] = "host";
67const char STATSREPORT_STUN_PORT_TYPE[] = "serverreflexive";
68const char STATSREPORT_PRFLX_PORT_TYPE[] = "peerreflexive";
69const char STATSREPORT_RELAY_PORT_TYPE[] = "relayed";
70
71// Strings used by the stats collector to report adapter types. This fits the
72// general stype of http://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats than what
73// AdapterTypeToString does.
74const char* STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_ETHERNET = "lan";
75const char* STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_WIFI = "wlan";
76const char* STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_WWAN = "wwan";
77const char* STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_VPN = "vpn";
78const char* STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_LOOPBACK = "loopback";
79const char* STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_WILDCARD = "wildcard";

81template <typename ValueType>
82struct TypeForAdd {
83 const StatsReport::StatsValueName name;
84 const ValueType& value;
85};
86
87typedef TypeForAdd<bool> BoolForAdd;
88typedef TypeForAdd<float> FloatForAdd;
89typedef TypeForAdd<int64_t> Int64ForAdd;
90typedef TypeForAdd<int> IntForAdd;
91
92StatsReport* AddTrackReport(StatsCollection* reports,
93 const std::string& track_id) {
94 // Adds an empty track report.
95 StatsReport::Id id(
96 StatsReport::NewTypedId(StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeTrack, track_id));
97 StatsReport* report = reports->ReplaceOrAddNew(id);
98 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTrackId, track_id);
99 return report;
100}
101
102template <class Track>
103void CreateTrackReport(const Track* track,
104 StatsCollection* reports,
105 TrackIdMap* track_ids) {
106 const std::string& track_id = track->id();
107 StatsReport* report = AddTrackReport(reports, track_id);
108 RTC_DCHECK(report != nullptr);
109 (*track_ids)[track_id] = report;
110}
111
112template <class TrackVector>
113void CreateTrackReports(const TrackVector& tracks,
114 StatsCollection* reports,
115 TrackIdMap* track_ids) {
116 for (const auto& track : tracks) {
117 CreateTrackReport(track.get(), reports, track_ids);
118 }
119}

121void ExtractCommonSendProperties(const cricket::MediaSenderInfo& info,
122 StatsReport* report,
123 bool use_standard_bytes_stats) {
124 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCodecName, info.codec_name);
125 int64_t bytes_sent = info.payload_bytes_sent;
126 if (!use_standard_bytes_stats) {
127 bytes_sent += info.header_and_padding_bytes_sent;
128 }
129 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameBytesSent, bytes_sent);
130 if (info.rtt_ms >= 0) {
131 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRtt, info.rtt_ms);
132 }
133}
134
135void ExtractCommonReceiveProperties(const cricket::MediaReceiverInfo& info,
136 StatsReport* report) {
137 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCodecName, info.codec_name);
138}
139
140void SetAudioProcessingStats(StatsReport* report,
141 bool typing_noise_detected,
142 const AudioProcessingStats& apm_stats) {
143 report->AddBoolean(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTypingNoiseState,
144 typing_noise_detected);
145 if (apm_stats.delay_median_ms) {
146 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameEchoDelayMedian,
147 *apm_stats.delay_median_ms);
148 }
149 if (apm_stats.delay_standard_deviation_ms) {
150 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameEchoDelayStdDev,
151 *apm_stats.delay_standard_deviation_ms);
152 }
153 if (apm_stats.echo_return_loss) {
154 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameEchoReturnLoss,
155 *apm_stats.echo_return_loss);
156 }
157 if (apm_stats.echo_return_loss_enhancement) {
158 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameEchoReturnLossEnhancement,
159 *apm_stats.echo_return_loss_enhancement);
160 }
161 if (apm_stats.residual_echo_likelihood) {
162 report->AddFloat(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameResidualEchoLikelihood,
163 static_cast<float>(*apm_stats.residual_echo_likelihood));
164 }
165 if (apm_stats.residual_echo_likelihood_recent_max) {
166 report->AddFloat(
167 StatsReport::kStatsValueNameResidualEchoLikelihoodRecentMax,
168 static_cast<float>(*apm_stats.residual_echo_likelihood_recent_max));
169 }
170 if (apm_stats.divergent_filter_fraction) {
171 report->AddFloat(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAecDivergentFilterFraction,
172 static_cast<float>(*apm_stats.divergent_filter_fraction));
173 }
174}

176void ExtractStats(const cricket::VoiceReceiverInfo& info,
177 StatsReport* report,
178 bool use_standard_bytes_stats) {
179 ExtractCommonReceiveProperties(info, report);
180 const FloatForAdd floats[] = {
181 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameExpandRate, info.expand_rate},
182 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSecondaryDecodedRate,
183 info.secondary_decoded_rate},
184 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSecondaryDiscardedRate,
185 info.secondary_discarded_rate},
186 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSpeechExpandRate, info.speech_expand_rate},
187 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAccelerateRate, info.accelerate_rate},
188 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePreemptiveExpandRate,
189 info.preemptive_expand_rate},
190 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTotalAudioEnergy, info.total_output_energy},
191 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTotalSamplesDuration,
192 info.total_output_duration}};
193
194 const IntForAdd ints[] = {
195 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCurrentDelayMs, info.delay_estimate_ms},
196 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDecodingCNG, info.decoding_cng},
197 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDecodingCTN, info.decoding_calls_to_neteq},
198 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDecodingCTSG,
199 info.decoding_calls_to_silence_generator},
200 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDecodingMutedOutput,
201 info.decoding_muted_output},
202 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDecodingNormal, info.decoding_normal},
203 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDecodingPLC, info.decoding_plc},
204 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDecodingPLCCNG, info.decoding_plc_cng},
205 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameJitterBufferMs, info.jitter_buffer_ms},
206 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameJitterReceived, info.jitter_ms},
207 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePacketsLost, info.packets_lost},
208 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePacketsReceived, info.packets_rcvd},
209 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePreferredJitterBufferMs,
210 info.jitter_buffer_preferred_ms},
211 };
212
213 for (const auto& f : floats)
214 report->AddFloat(f.name, f.value);
215
216 for (const auto& i : ints)
217 report->AddInt(i.name, i.value);
218 if (info.audio_level >= 0) {
219 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAudioOutputLevel,
220 info.audio_level);
221 }
222 if (info.decoding_codec_plc)
223 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDecodingCodecPLC,
224 info.decoding_codec_plc);
225
226 int64_t bytes_rcvd = info.payload_bytes_rcvd;
227 if (!use_standard_bytes_stats) {
228 bytes_rcvd += info.header_and_padding_bytes_rcvd;
229 }
230 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameBytesReceived, bytes_rcvd);
231 if (info.capture_start_ntp_time_ms >= 0) {
232 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCaptureStartNtpTimeMs,
233 info.capture_start_ntp_time_ms);
234 }
235 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameMediaType, "audio");
236}

238void ExtractStats(const cricket::VoiceSenderInfo& info,
239 StatsReport* report,
240 bool use_standard_bytes_stats) {
241 ExtractCommonSendProperties(info, report, use_standard_bytes_stats);
242
243 SetAudioProcessingStats(report, info.typing_noise_detected,
244 info.apm_statistics);
245
246 const FloatForAdd floats[] = {
247 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTotalAudioEnergy, info.total_input_energy},
248 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTotalSamplesDuration,
249 info.total_input_duration}};
250
251 RTC_DCHECK_GE(info.audio_level, 0);
252 const IntForAdd ints[] = {
253 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAudioInputLevel, info.audio_level},
254 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameJitterReceived, info.jitter_ms},
255 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePacketsLost, info.packets_lost},
256 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePacketsSent, info.packets_sent},
257 };
258
259 for (const auto& f : floats) {
260 report->AddFloat(f.name, f.value);
261 }
262
263 for (const auto& i : ints) {
264 if (i.value >= 0) {
265 report->AddInt(i.name, i.value);
266 }
267 }
268 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameMediaType, "audio");
269 if (info.ana_statistics.bitrate_action_counter) {
270 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAnaBitrateActionCounter,
271 *info.ana_statistics.bitrate_action_counter);
272 }
273 if (info.ana_statistics.channel_action_counter) {
274 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAnaChannelActionCounter,
275 *info.ana_statistics.channel_action_counter);
276 }
277 if (info.ana_statistics.dtx_action_counter) {
278 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAnaDtxActionCounter,
279 *info.ana_statistics.dtx_action_counter);
280 }
281 if (info.ana_statistics.fec_action_counter) {
282 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAnaFecActionCounter,
283 *info.ana_statistics.fec_action_counter);
284 }
285 if (info.ana_statistics.frame_length_increase_counter) {
286 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAnaFrameLengthIncreaseCounter,
287 *info.ana_statistics.frame_length_increase_counter);
288 }
289 if (info.ana_statistics.frame_length_decrease_counter) {
290 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAnaFrameLengthDecreaseCounter,
291 *info.ana_statistics.frame_length_decrease_counter);
292 }
293 if (info.ana_statistics.uplink_packet_loss_fraction) {
294 report->AddFloat(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAnaUplinkPacketLossFraction,
295 *info.ana_statistics.uplink_packet_loss_fraction);
296 }
297}

299void ExtractStats(const cricket::VideoReceiverInfo& info,
300 StatsReport* report,
301 bool use_standard_bytes_stats) {
302 ExtractCommonReceiveProperties(info, report);
303 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCodecImplementationName,
304 info.decoder_implementation_name);
305 int64_t bytes_rcvd = info.payload_bytes_rcvd;
306 if (!use_standard_bytes_stats) {
307 bytes_rcvd += info.header_and_padding_bytes_rcvd;
308 }
309 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameBytesReceived, bytes_rcvd);
310 if (info.capture_start_ntp_time_ms >= 0) {
311 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCaptureStartNtpTimeMs,
312 info.capture_start_ntp_time_ms);
313 }
314 if (info.first_frame_received_to_decoded_ms >= 0) {
315 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFirstFrameReceivedToDecodedMs,
316 info.first_frame_received_to_decoded_ms);
317 }
318 if (info.qp_sum)
319 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameQpSum, *info.qp_sum);
320
321 const IntForAdd ints[] = {
322 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCurrentDelayMs, info.current_delay_ms},
323 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDecodeMs, info.decode_ms},
324 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFirsSent, info.firs_sent},
325 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameHeightReceived, info.frame_height},
326 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameRateDecoded, info.framerate_decoded},
327 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameRateOutput, info.framerate_output},
328 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameRateReceived, info.framerate_rcvd},
329 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameWidthReceived, info.frame_width},
330 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameJitterBufferMs, info.jitter_buffer_ms},
331 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameMaxDecodeMs, info.max_decode_ms},
332 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameMinPlayoutDelayMs,
333 info.min_playout_delay_ms},
334 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameNacksSent, info.nacks_sent},
335 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePacketsLost, info.packets_lost},
336 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePacketsReceived, info.packets_rcvd},
337 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePlisSent, info.plis_sent},
338 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRenderDelayMs, info.render_delay_ms},
339 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTargetDelayMs, info.target_delay_ms},
340 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFramesDecoded, info.frames_decoded},
341 };
342
343 for (const auto& i : ints)
344 report->AddInt(i.name, i.value);
345 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameMediaType, "video");
346
347 if (info.timing_frame_info) {
348 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTimingFrameInfo,
349 info.timing_frame_info->ToString());
350 }
351
352 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameInterframeDelayMaxMs,
353 info.interframe_delay_max_ms);
354
355 report->AddString(
356 StatsReport::kStatsValueNameContentType,
357 webrtc::videocontenttypehelpers::ToString(info.content_type));
358}

380 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameEncodeUsagePercent,
381 info.encode_usage_percent},
382 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFirsReceived, info.firs_rcvd},
383 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameHeightSent, info.send_frame_height},
384 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameRateInput, info.framerate_input},
385 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameRateSent, info.framerate_sent},
386 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameWidthSent, info.send_frame_width},
387 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameNacksReceived, info.nacks_rcvd},
388 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePacketsLost, info.packets_lost},
389 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePacketsSent, info.packets_sent},
390 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePlisReceived, info.plis_rcvd},
391 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFramesEncoded, info.frames_encoded},
392 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameHugeFramesSent, info.huge_frames_sent},
393 };
394
395 for (const auto& i : ints)
396 report->AddInt(i.name, i.value);
397 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameMediaType, "video");
398 report->AddString(
399 StatsReport::kStatsValueNameContentType,
400 webrtc::videocontenttypehelpers::ToString(info.content_type));
401}

436std::string GetTrackIdBySsrc(
437 uint32_t ssrc,
438 StatsReport::Direction direction,
439 const std::map<uint32_t, std::string>& track_id_by_ssrc) {
440 auto it = track_id_by_ssrc.find(ssrc);
441 if (it != track_id_by_ssrc.end()) {
442 return it->second;
443 }
444 if (direction == StatsReport::kReceive) {
445 // If the track ID was not found, this might be an unsignaled receive
446 // SSRC, so try looking up by the special SSRC 0.
447 it = track_id_by_ssrc.find(0);
448 if (it != track_id_by_ssrc.end()) {
449 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Assuming SSRC=" << ssrc
450 << " is an unsignalled receive stream corresponding "
451 "to the RtpReceiver with track ID \""
452 << it->second << "\".";
453 return it->second;
454 }
455 }
456 return "";
457}
458
459// Template to extract stats from a data vector.
460// In order to use the template, the functions that are called from it,
461// ExtractStats and ExtractRemoteStats, must be defined and overloaded
462// for each type.
463template <typename T>
464void ExtractStatsFromList(
465 const std::vector<T>& data,
466 const StatsReport::Id& transport_id,
467 StatsCollector* collector,
468 StatsReport::Direction direction,
469 const std::map<uint32_t, std::string>& track_id_by_ssrc) {
470 for (const auto& d : data) {
471 uint32_t ssrc = d.ssrc();
472 std::string track_id = GetTrackIdBySsrc(ssrc, direction, track_id_by_ssrc);
473 // Each track can have stats for both local and remote objects.
474 // TODO(hta): Handle the case of multiple SSRCs per object.
475 StatsReport* report =
476 collector->PrepareReport(true, ssrc, track_id, transport_id, direction);
477 if (report)
478 ExtractStats(d, report, collector->UseStandardBytesStats());
479
480 if (!d.remote_stats.empty()) {
481 report = collector->PrepareReport(false, ssrc, track_id, transport_id,
482 direction);
483 if (report)
484 ExtractRemoteStats(d, report);
485 }
486 }
487}

491const char* IceCandidateTypeToStatsType(const std::string& candidate_type) {
492 if (candidate_type == cricket::LOCAL_PORT_TYPE) {
493 return STATSREPORT_LOCAL_PORT_TYPE;
494 }
495 if (candidate_type == cricket::STUN_PORT_TYPE) {
496 return STATSREPORT_STUN_PORT_TYPE;
497 }
498 if (candidate_type == cricket::PRFLX_PORT_TYPE) {
499 return STATSREPORT_PRFLX_PORT_TYPE;
500 }
501 if (candidate_type == cricket::RELAY_PORT_TYPE) {
502 return STATSREPORT_RELAY_PORT_TYPE;
503 }
504 RTC_NOTREACHED();
505 return "unknown";
506}
507
508const char* AdapterTypeToStatsType(rtc::AdapterType type) {
509 switch (type) {
510 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_UNKNOWN:
511 return "unknown";
512 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_ETHERNET:
513 return STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_ETHERNET;
514 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_WIFI:
515 return STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_WIFI;
516 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR:
517 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_2G:
518 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_3G:
519 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_4G:
520 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_5G:
521 return STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_WWAN;
522 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_VPN:
523 return STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_VPN;
524 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_LOOPBACK:
525 return STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_LOOPBACK;
526 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_ANY:
527 return STATSREPORT_ADAPTER_TYPE_WILDCARD;
528 default:
529 RTC_NOTREACHED();
530 return "";
531 }

534StatsCollector::StatsCollector(PeerConnectionInternal* pc)
535 : pc_(pc),
536 stats_gathering_started_(0),
537 use_standard_bytes_stats_(
538 webrtc::field_trial::IsEnabled(kUseStandardBytesStats)) {
539 RTC_DCHECK(pc_);
540}

542StatsCollector::~StatsCollector() {

546// Wallclock time in ms.
547double StatsCollector::GetTimeNow() {
548 return static_cast<double>(rtc::TimeUTCMillis());
549}
550
551// Adds a MediaStream with tracks that can be used as a |selector| in a call
552// to GetStats.
553void StatsCollector::AddStream(MediaStreamInterface* stream) {
554 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
555 RTC_DCHECK(stream != NULL);
556
557 CreateTrackReports<AudioTrackVector>(stream->GetAudioTracks(), &reports_,
558 &track_ids_);
559 CreateTrackReports<VideoTrackVector>(stream->GetVideoTracks(), &reports_,
560 &track_ids_);
561}
562
563void StatsCollector::AddTrack(MediaStreamTrackInterface* track) {
564 if (track->kind() == MediaStreamTrackInterface::kAudioKind) {
565 CreateTrackReport(static_cast<AudioTrackInterface*>(track), &reports_,
566 &track_ids_);
567 } else if (track->kind() == MediaStreamTrackInterface::kVideoKind) {
568 CreateTrackReport(static_cast<VideoTrackInterface*>(track), &reports_,
569 &track_ids_);
570 } else {
571 RTC_NOTREACHED() << "Illegal track kind";
572 }
573}
574
575void StatsCollector::AddLocalAudioTrack(AudioTrackInterface* audio_track,
576 uint32_t ssrc) {
577 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
578 RTC_DCHECK(audio_track != NULL);
579#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
580 for (const auto& track : local_audio_tracks_)
581 RTC_DCHECK(track.first != audio_track || track.second != ssrc);
582#endif
583
584 local_audio_tracks_.push_back(std::make_pair(audio_track, ssrc));
585
586 // Create the kStatsReportTypeTrack report for the new track if there is no
587 // report yet.
588 StatsReport::Id id(StatsReport::NewTypedId(StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeTrack,
589 audio_track->id()));
590 StatsReport* report = reports_.Find(id);
591 if (!report) {
592 report = reports_.InsertNew(id);
593 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTrackId, audio_track->id());
594 }
595}
596
597void StatsCollector::RemoveLocalAudioTrack(AudioTrackInterface* audio_track,
598 uint32_t ssrc) {
599 RTC_DCHECK(audio_track != NULL);
600 local_audio_tracks_.erase(
601 std::remove_if(
602 local_audio_tracks_.begin(), local_audio_tracks_.end(),
603 [audio_track, ssrc](const LocalAudioTrackVector::value_type& track) {
604 return track.first == audio_track && track.second == ssrc;
605 }),
606 local_audio_tracks_.end());
607}
608
609void StatsCollector::GetStats(MediaStreamTrackInterface* track,
610 StatsReports* reports) {
611 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
612 RTC_DCHECK(reports != NULL);
613 RTC_DCHECK(reports->empty());
614
615 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
616
617 if (!track) {
618 reports->reserve(reports_.size());
619 for (auto* r : reports_)
620 reports->push_back(r);
621 return;
622 }
623
624 StatsReport* report = reports_.Find(StatsReport::NewTypedId(
625 StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeSession, pc_->session_id()));
626 if (report)
627 reports->push_back(report);
628
629 report = reports_.Find(
630 StatsReport::NewTypedId(StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeTrack, track->id()));
631
632 if (!report)
633 return;
634
635 reports->push_back(report);
636
637 std::string track_id;
638 for (const auto* r : reports_) {
639 if (r->type() != StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeSsrc)
640 continue;
641
642 const StatsReport::Value* v =
643 r->FindValue(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTrackId);
644 if (v && v->string_val() == track->id())
645 reports->push_back(r);
646 }
647}
648
649void StatsCollector::UpdateStats(
650 PeerConnectionInterface::StatsOutputLevel level) {
651 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
652 // Calls to UpdateStats() that occur less than kMinGatherStatsPeriodMs apart
653 // will be ignored. Using a monotonic clock specifically for this, while using
654 // a UTC clock for the reports themselves.
655 const int64_t kMinGatherStatsPeriodMs = 50;
656 int64_t cache_now_ms = rtc::TimeMillis();
657 if (cache_timestamp_ms_ != 0 &&
658 cache_timestamp_ms_ + kMinGatherStatsPeriodMs > cache_now_ms) {
659 return;
660 }
661 cache_timestamp_ms_ = cache_now_ms;
662 stats_gathering_started_ = GetTimeNow();
663
664 // TODO(tommi): ExtractSessionInfo now has a single hop to the network thread
665 // to fetch stats, then applies them on the signaling thread. See if we need
666 // to do this synchronously or if updating the stats without blocking is safe.
667 std::map<std::string, std::string> transport_names_by_mid =
668 ExtractSessionInfo();
669
670 // TODO(tommi): All of these hop over to the worker thread to fetch
671 // information. We could post a task to run all of these and post
672 // the information back to the signaling thread where we can create and
673 // update stats reports. That would also clean up the threading story a bit
674 // since we'd be creating/updating the stats report objects consistently on
675 // the same thread (this class has no locks right now).
676 ExtractBweInfo();
677 ExtractMediaInfo(transport_names_by_mid);
678 ExtractSenderInfo();
679 ExtractDataInfo();
680 UpdateTrackReports();
681}
682
683StatsReport* StatsCollector::PrepareReport(bool local,
684 uint32_t ssrc,
685 const std::string& track_id,
686 const StatsReport::Id& transport_id,
687 StatsReport::Direction direction) {
688 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
689 StatsReport::Id id(StatsReport::NewIdWithDirection(
690 local ? StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeSsrc
691 : StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeRemoteSsrc,
692 rtc::ToString(ssrc), direction));
693 StatsReport* report = reports_.Find(id);
694 if (!report) {
695 report = reports_.InsertNew(id);
696 }
697
698 // FYI - for remote reports, the timestamp will be overwritten later.
699 report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
700
701 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSsrc, ssrc);
702 if (!track_id.empty()) {
703 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTrackId, track_id);
704 }
705 // Add the mapping of SSRC to transport.
706 report->AddId(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTransportId, transport_id);
707 return report;
708}

710StatsReport* StatsCollector::PrepareADMReport() {
711 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
712 StatsReport::Id id(StatsReport::NewTypedId(
713 StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeSession, pc_->session_id()));
714 StatsReport* report = reports_.FindOrAddNew(id);
715 return report;
716}

718bool StatsCollector::IsValidTrack(const std::string& track_id) {
719 return reports_.Find(StatsReport::NewTypedId(
720 StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeTrack, track_id)) != nullptr;
721}
722
723StatsReport* StatsCollector::AddCertificateReports(
724 std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLCertificateStats> cert_stats) {
725 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
726
727 StatsReport* first_report = nullptr;
728 StatsReport* prev_report = nullptr;
729 for (rtc::SSLCertificateStats* stats = cert_stats.get(); stats;
730 stats = stats->issuer.get()) {
731 StatsReport::Id id(StatsReport::NewTypedId(
732 StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeCertificate, stats->fingerprint));
733
734 StatsReport* report = reports_.ReplaceOrAddNew(id);
735 report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
736 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFingerprint,
737 stats->fingerprint);
738 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFingerprintAlgorithm,
739 stats->fingerprint_algorithm);
740 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDer,
741 stats->base64_certificate);
742 if (!first_report)
743 first_report = report;
744 else
745 prev_report->AddId(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameIssuerId, id);
746 prev_report = report;
747 }
748 return first_report;
749}
750
751StatsReport* StatsCollector::AddConnectionInfoReport(
752 const std::string& content_name,
753 int component,
754 int connection_id,
755 const StatsReport::Id& channel_report_id,
756 const cricket::ConnectionInfo& info) {
757 StatsReport::Id id(
758 StatsReport::NewCandidatePairId(content_name, component, connection_id));
759 StatsReport* report = reports_.ReplaceOrAddNew(id);
760 report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
761
762 const BoolForAdd bools[] = {
763 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameActiveConnection, info.best_connection},
764 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameReceiving, info.receiving},
765 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameWritable, info.writable},
766 };
767 for (const auto& b : bools)
768 report->AddBoolean(b.name, b.value);
769
770 report->AddId(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameChannelId, channel_report_id);
771 cricket::CandidateStats local_candidate_stats(info.local_candidate);
772 cricket::CandidateStats remote_candidate_stats(info.remote_candidate);
773 report->AddId(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameLocalCandidateId,
774 AddCandidateReport(local_candidate_stats, true)->id());
775 report->AddId(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRemoteCandidateId,
776 AddCandidateReport(remote_candidate_stats, false)->id());
777
778 const Int64ForAdd int64s[] = {
779 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameBytesReceived, info.recv_total_bytes},
780 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameBytesSent, info.sent_total_bytes},
781 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNamePacketsSent, info.sent_total_packets},
782 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRtt, info.rtt},
783 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSendPacketsDiscarded,
784 info.sent_discarded_packets},
785 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSentPingRequestsTotal,
786 info.sent_ping_requests_total},
787 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSentPingRequestsBeforeFirstResponse,
788 info.sent_ping_requests_before_first_response},
789 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSentPingResponses, info.sent_ping_responses},
790 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRecvPingRequests, info.recv_ping_requests},
791 {StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRecvPingResponses, info.recv_ping_responses},
792 };
793 for (const auto& i : int64s)
794 report->AddInt64(i.name, i.value);
795
796 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameLocalAddress,
797 info.local_candidate.address().ToString());
798 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameLocalCandidateType,
799 info.local_candidate.type());
800 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRemoteAddress,
801 info.remote_candidate.address().ToString());
802 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRemoteCandidateType,
803 info.remote_candidate.type());
804 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTransportType,
805 info.local_candidate.protocol());
806
807 return report;
808}
809
810StatsReport* StatsCollector::AddCandidateReport(
811 const cricket::CandidateStats& candidate_stats,
812 bool local) {
813 const auto& candidate = candidate_stats.candidate;
814 StatsReport::Id id(StatsReport::NewCandidateId(local, candidate.id()));
815 StatsReport* report = reports_.Find(id);
816 if (!report) {
817 report = reports_.InsertNew(id);
818 report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
819 if (local) {
820 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCandidateNetworkType,
821 AdapterTypeToStatsType(candidate.network_type()));
822 }
823 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCandidateIPAddress,
824 candidate.address().ipaddr().ToString());
825 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCandidatePortNumber,
826 candidate.address().PortAsString());
827 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCandidatePriority,
828 candidate.priority());
829 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCandidateType,
830 IceCandidateTypeToStatsType(candidate.type()));
831 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameCandidateTransportType,
832 candidate.protocol());
833 }
834 report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
835
836 if (local && candidate_stats.stun_stats.has_value()) {
837 const auto& stun_stats = candidate_stats.stun_stats.value();
838 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSentStunKeepaliveRequests,
839 stun_stats.stun_binding_requests_sent);
840 report->AddInt64(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRecvStunKeepaliveResponses,
841 stun_stats.stun_binding_responses_received);
842 report->AddFloat(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameStunKeepaliveRttTotal,
843 stun_stats.stun_binding_rtt_ms_total);
844 report->AddFloat(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameStunKeepaliveRttSquaredTotal,
845 stun_stats.stun_binding_rtt_ms_squared_total);
846 }
847
848 return report;
849}
850
851std::map<std::string, std::string> StatsCollector::ExtractSessionInfo() {
852 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
853
854 SessionStats stats;
855 auto transceivers = pc_->GetTransceiversInternal();
856 pc_->network_thread()->Invoke<void>(
857 RTC_FROM_HERE, [&, sctp_transport_name = pc_->sctp_transport_name(),
858 sctp_mid = pc_->sctp_mid()]() mutable {
859 stats = ExtractSessionInfo_n(
860 transceivers, std::move(sctp_transport_name), std::move(sctp_mid));
861 });
862
863 ExtractSessionInfo_s(stats);
864
865 return std::move(stats.transport_names_by_mid);
866}
867
868StatsCollector::SessionStats StatsCollector::ExtractSessionInfo_n(
869 const std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<
870 RtpTransceiverProxyWithInternal<RtpTransceiver>>>& transceivers,
871 absl::optional<std::string> sctp_transport_name,
872 absl::optional<std::string> sctp_mid) {
873 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->network_thread());
874 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
875 SessionStats stats;
876 stats.candidate_stats = pc_->GetPooledCandidateStats();
877 for (auto& transceiver : transceivers) {
878 cricket::ChannelInterface* channel = transceiver->internal()->channel();
879 if (channel) {
880 stats.transport_names_by_mid[channel->content_name()] =
881 channel->transport_name();
882 }
883 }
884
885 if (sctp_transport_name) {
886 RTC_DCHECK(sctp_mid);
887 stats.transport_names_by_mid[*sctp_mid] = *sctp_transport_name;
888 }
889
890 std::set<std::string> transport_names;
891 for (const auto& entry : stats.transport_names_by_mid) {
892 transport_names.insert(entry.second);
893 }
894
895 std::map<std::string, cricket::TransportStats> transport_stats_by_name =
896 pc_->GetTransportStatsByNames(transport_names);
897
898 for (auto& entry : transport_stats_by_name) {
899 stats.transport_stats.emplace_back(entry.first, std::move(entry.second));
900 TransportStats& transport = stats.transport_stats.back();
901
902 // Attempt to get a copy of the certificates from the transport and
903 // expose them in stats reports. All channels in a transport share the
904 // same local and remote certificates.
905 //
906 StatsReport::Id local_cert_report_id, remote_cert_report_id;
907 rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate> certificate;
908 if (pc_->GetLocalCertificate(transport.name, &certificate)) {
909 transport.local_cert_stats =
910 certificate->GetSSLCertificateChain().GetStats();
911 }
912
913 std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLCertChain> remote_cert_chain =
914 pc_->GetRemoteSSLCertChain(transport.name);
915 if (remote_cert_chain) {
916 transport.remote_cert_stats = remote_cert_chain->GetStats();
917 }
918 }
919
920 return stats;
921}
922
923void StatsCollector::ExtractSessionInfo_s(SessionStats& session_stats) {
924 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
925 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
926
927 StatsReport::Id id(StatsReport::NewTypedId(
928 StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeSession, pc_->session_id()));
929 StatsReport* report = reports_.ReplaceOrAddNew(id);
930 report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
931 report->AddBoolean(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameInitiator,
932 pc_->initial_offerer());
933
934 for (const cricket::CandidateStats& stats : session_stats.candidate_stats) {
935 AddCandidateReport(stats, true);
936 }
937
938 for (auto& transport : session_stats.transport_stats) {
939 // Attempt to get a copy of the certificates from the transport and
940 // expose them in stats reports. All channels in a transport share the
941 // same local and remote certificates.
942 //
943 StatsReport::Id local_cert_report_id, remote_cert_report_id;
944 if (transport.local_cert_stats) {
945 StatsReport* r =
946 AddCertificateReports(std::move(transport.local_cert_stats));
947 if (r)
948 local_cert_report_id = r->id();
949 }
950
951 if (transport.remote_cert_stats) {
952 StatsReport* r =
953 AddCertificateReports(std::move(transport.remote_cert_stats));
954 if (r)
955 remote_cert_report_id = r->id();
956 }
957
958 for (const auto& channel_iter : transport.stats.channel_stats) {
959 StatsReport::Id id(
960 StatsReport::NewComponentId(transport.name, channel_iter.component));
961 StatsReport* channel_report = reports_.ReplaceOrAddNew(id);
962 channel_report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
963 channel_report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameComponent,
964 channel_iter.component);
965 if (local_cert_report_id.get()) {
966 channel_report->AddId(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameLocalCertificateId,
967 local_cert_report_id);
968 }
969 if (remote_cert_report_id.get()) {
970 channel_report->AddId(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameRemoteCertificateId,
971 remote_cert_report_id);
972 }
973 int srtp_crypto_suite = channel_iter.srtp_crypto_suite;
974 if (srtp_crypto_suite != rtc::SRTP_INVALID_CRYPTO_SUITE &&
975 rtc::SrtpCryptoSuiteToName(srtp_crypto_suite).length()) {
976 channel_report->AddString(
977 StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSrtpCipher,
978 rtc::SrtpCryptoSuiteToName(srtp_crypto_suite));
979 }
980 int ssl_cipher_suite = channel_iter.ssl_cipher_suite;
981 if (ssl_cipher_suite != rtc::TLS_NULL_WITH_NULL_NULL &&
982 rtc::SSLStreamAdapter::SslCipherSuiteToName(ssl_cipher_suite)
983 .length()) {
984 channel_report->AddString(
985 StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDtlsCipher,
986 rtc::SSLStreamAdapter::SslCipherSuiteToName(ssl_cipher_suite));
987 }
988
989 // Collect stats for non-pooled candidates. Note that the reports
990 // generated here supersedes the candidate reports generated in
991 // AddConnectionInfoReport below, and they may report candidates that are
992 // not paired. Also, the candidate report generated in
993 // AddConnectionInfoReport do not report port stats like StunStats.
994 for (const cricket::CandidateStats& stats :
995 channel_iter.ice_transport_stats.candidate_stats_list) {
996 AddCandidateReport(stats, true);
997 }
998
999 int connection_id = 0;
1000 for (const cricket::ConnectionInfo& info :
1001 channel_iter.ice_transport_stats.connection_infos) {
1002 StatsReport* connection_report = AddConnectionInfoReport(
1003 transport.name, channel_iter.component, connection_id++,
1004 channel_report->id(), info);
1005 if (info.best_connection) {
1006 channel_report->AddId(
1007 StatsReport::kStatsValueNameSelectedCandidatePairId,
1008 connection_report->id());
1009 }
1010 }
1011 }
1012 }
1013}
1014
1015void StatsCollector::ExtractBweInfo() {
1016 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
1017
1018 if (pc_->signaling_state() == PeerConnectionInterface::kClosed)
1019 return;
1020
1021 webrtc::Call::Stats call_stats = pc_->GetCallStats();
1022 cricket::BandwidthEstimationInfo bwe_info;
1023 bwe_info.available_send_bandwidth = call_stats.send_bandwidth_bps;
1024 bwe_info.available_recv_bandwidth = call_stats.recv_bandwidth_bps;
1025 bwe_info.bucket_delay = call_stats.pacer_delay_ms;
1026
1027 // Fill in target encoder bitrate, actual encoder bitrate, rtx bitrate, etc.
1028 // TODO(holmer): Also fill this in for audio.
1029 auto transceivers = pc_->GetTransceiversInternal();
1030 std::vector<cricket::VideoChannel*> video_channels;
1031 for (const auto& transceiver : transceivers) {
1032 if (transceiver->media_type() != cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
1033 continue;
1034 }
1035 auto* video_channel =
1036 static_cast<cricket::VideoChannel*>(transceiver->internal()->channel());
1037 if (video_channel) {
1038 video_channels.push_back(video_channel);
1039 }
1040 }
1041
1042 if (!video_channels.empty()) {
1043 pc_->worker_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
1044 for (const auto& channel : video_channels) {
1045 channel->FillBitrateInfo(&bwe_info);
1046 }
1047 });
1048 }
1049
1050 StatsReport::Id report_id(StatsReport::NewBandwidthEstimationId());
1051 StatsReport* report = reports_.FindOrAddNew(report_id);
1052 ExtractStats(bwe_info, stats_gathering_started_, report);
1053}

1083 ExtractStatsFromList(sender_data, transport_id, collector,
1084 StatsReport::kSend, sender_track_id_by_ssrc);
1085 }

1159
1160void StatsCollector::ExtractMediaInfo(
1161 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& transport_names_by_mid) {
1162 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
1163
1164 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<MediaChannelStatsGatherer>> gatherers;
1165
1166 auto transceivers = pc_->GetTransceiversInternal();
1167 {
1168 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1169 for (const auto& transceiver : transceivers) {
1170 cricket::ChannelInterface* channel = transceiver->internal()->channel();
1171 if (!channel) {
1172 continue;
1173 }
1174 std::unique_ptr<MediaChannelStatsGatherer> gatherer =
1175 CreateMediaChannelStatsGatherer(channel->media_channel());
1176 gatherer->mid = channel->content_name();
1177 gatherer->transport_name = transport_names_by_mid.at(gatherer->mid);
1178
1179 for (const auto& sender : transceiver->internal()->senders()) {
1180 auto track = sender->track();
1181 std::string track_id = (track ? track->id() : "");
1182 gatherer->sender_track_id_by_ssrc.insert(
1183 std::make_pair(sender->ssrc(), track_id));
1184 }
1185
1186 // Populating `receiver_track_id_by_ssrc` will be done on the worker
1187 // thread as the `ssrc` property of the receiver needs to be accessed
1188 // there.
1189
1190 gatherers.push_back(std::move(gatherer));
1191 }
1192 }
1193
1194 pc_->worker_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
1195 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1196 // Populate `receiver_track_id_by_ssrc` for the gatherers.
1197 int i = 0;
1198 for (const auto& transceiver : transceivers) {
1199 cricket::ChannelInterface* channel = transceiver->internal()->channel();
1200 if (!channel)
1201 continue;
1202 MediaChannelStatsGatherer* gatherer = gatherers[i++].get();
1203 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(gatherer->mid, channel->content_name());
1204
1205 for (const auto& receiver : transceiver->internal()->receivers()) {
1206 gatherer->receiver_track_id_by_ssrc.insert(std::make_pair(
1207 receiver->internal()->ssrc(), receiver->track()->id()));
1208 }
1209 }
1210
1211 for (auto it = gatherers.begin(); it != gatherers.end();
1212 /* incremented manually */) {
1213 MediaChannelStatsGatherer* gatherer = it->get();
1214 if (!gatherer->GetStatsOnWorkerThread()) {
1215 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get media channel stats for mid="
1216 << gatherer->mid;
1217 it = gatherers.erase(it);
1218 continue;
1219 }
1220 ++it;
1221 }
1222 });
1223
1224 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1225
1226 bool has_remote_audio = false;
1227 for (const auto& gatherer : gatherers) {
1228 gatherer->ExtractStats(this);
1229 has_remote_audio |= gatherer->HasRemoteAudio();
1230 }
1231
1232 UpdateStatsFromExistingLocalAudioTracks(has_remote_audio);
1233}
1234
1235void StatsCollector::ExtractSenderInfo() {
1236 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
1237
1238 for (const auto& sender : pc_->GetSenders()) {
1239 // TODO(nisse): SSRC == 0 currently means none. Delete check when
1240 // that is fixed.
1241 if (!sender->ssrc()) {
1242 continue;
1243 }
1244 const rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamTrackInterface> track(sender->track());
1245 if (!track || track->kind() != MediaStreamTrackInterface::kVideoKind) {
1246 continue;
1247 }
1248 // Safe, because kind() == kVideoKind implies a subclass of
1249 // VideoTrackInterface; see mediastreaminterface.h.
1250 VideoTrackSourceInterface* source =
1251 static_cast<VideoTrackInterface*>(track.get())->GetSource();
1252
1253 VideoTrackSourceInterface::Stats stats;
1254 if (!source->GetStats(&stats)) {
1255 continue;
1256 }
1257 const StatsReport::Id stats_id = StatsReport::NewIdWithDirection(
1258 StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeSsrc, rtc::ToString(sender->ssrc()),
1259 StatsReport::kSend);
1260 StatsReport* report = reports_.FindOrAddNew(stats_id);
1261 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameWidthInput,
1262 stats.input_width);
1263 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameFrameHeightInput,
1264 stats.input_height);
1265 }
1266}
1267
1268void StatsCollector::ExtractDataInfo() {
1269 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
1270
1271 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1272
1273 std::vector<DataChannelStats> data_stats = pc_->GetDataChannelStats();
1274 for (const auto& stats : data_stats) {
1275 StatsReport::Id id(StatsReport::NewTypedIntId(
1276 StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeDataChannel, stats.id));
1277 StatsReport* report = reports_.ReplaceOrAddNew(id);
1278 report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
1279 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameLabel, stats.label);
1280 // Filter out the initial id (-1).
1281 if (stats.id >= 0) {
1282 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameDataChannelId, stats.id);
1283 }
1284 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameProtocol, stats.protocol);
1285 report->AddString(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameState,
1286 DataChannelInterface::DataStateString(stats.state));
1287 }
1288}
1289
1290StatsReport* StatsCollector::GetReport(const StatsReport::StatsType& type,
1291 const std::string& id,
1292 StatsReport::Direction direction) {
1293 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
1294 RTC_DCHECK(type == StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeSsrc ||
1295 type == StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeRemoteSsrc);
1296 return reports_.Find(StatsReport::NewIdWithDirection(type, id, direction));
1297}
1298
1299void StatsCollector::UpdateStatsFromExistingLocalAudioTracks(
1300 bool has_remote_tracks) {
1301 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
1302 // Loop through the existing local audio tracks.
1303 for (const auto& it : local_audio_tracks_) {
1304 AudioTrackInterface* track = it.first;
1305 uint32_t ssrc = it.second;
1306 StatsReport* report = GetReport(StatsReport::kStatsReportTypeSsrc,
1307 rtc::ToString(ssrc), StatsReport::kSend);
1308 if (report == NULL) {
1309 // This can happen if a local audio track is added to a stream on the
1310 // fly and the report has not been set up yet. Do nothing in this case.
1311 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Stats report does not exist for ssrc " << ssrc;
1312 continue;
1313 }
1314
1315 // The same ssrc can be used by both local and remote audio tracks.
1316 const StatsReport::Value* v =
1317 report->FindValue(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameTrackId);
1318 if (!v || v->string_val() != track->id())
1319 continue;
1320
1321 report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
1322 UpdateReportFromAudioTrack(track, report, has_remote_tracks);
1323 }
1324}
1325
1326void StatsCollector::UpdateReportFromAudioTrack(AudioTrackInterface* track,
1327 StatsReport* report,
1328 bool has_remote_tracks) {
1329 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
1330 RTC_DCHECK(track != NULL);
1331
1332 // Don't overwrite report values if they're not available.
1333 int signal_level;
1334 if (track->GetSignalLevel(&signal_level)) {
1335 RTC_DCHECK_GE(signal_level, 0);
1336 report->AddInt(StatsReport::kStatsValueNameAudioInputLevel, signal_level);
1337 }
1338
1339 auto audio_processor(track->GetAudioProcessor());
1340
1341 if (audio_processor.get()) {
1342 AudioProcessorInterface::AudioProcessorStatistics stats =
1343 audio_processor->GetStats(has_remote_tracks);
1344
1345 SetAudioProcessingStats(report, stats.typing_noise_detected,
1346 stats.apm_statistics);
1347 }
1348}
1349
1350void StatsCollector::UpdateTrackReports() {
1351 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_->signaling_thread());
1352
1353 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1354
1355 for (const auto& entry : track_ids_) {
1356 StatsReport* report = entry.second;
1357 report->set_timestamp(stats_gathering_started_);
1358 }
1359}

1362 cache_timestamp_ms_ = 0;
1363}
